# Install MySQL on Windows

1. Download MySQL Installer
Go to: https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/installer/

Choose MySQL Installer for Windows (full or web)

2. Run the Installer
Select “Server Only” or “Developer Default” setup

Click Next

3. Check for Requirements
Installer may download missing packages (Visual C++ Redistributable, etc.)

4. Configure MySQL Server
Choose version (MySQL 8.0.x)

Configure:

Port: 3306 (default)

Authentication: Use strong password

Accounts: Set root password and optionally add other users

5. Set as Windows Service
Enable “Start MySQL Server at system startup”

6. Apply Configuration
Installer applies all changes and starts MySQL service

7. (Optional) Install MySQL Workbench
GUI for managing and querying your databases



Install MySQL on Linux

✅ Ubuntu / Debian
1. Update Packages
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y

2. Install MySQL Server
sudo apt install mysql-server -y

3. Secure Installation
sudo mysql_secure_installation

Set root password
Remove anonymous users
Disable remote root login (if needed)
Remove test database
Reload privilege tables

4. Start & Enable MySQL
sudo systemctl start mysql
sudo systemctl enable mysql

5. Login to MySQL
sudo mysql -u root -p

✅ CentOS / RHEL / AlmaLinux
1. Add MySQL Yum Repo
sudo yum install https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql80-community-release-el8-1.noarch.rpm

2. Install MySQL Server
sudo yum install mysql-server -y

3. Start & Enable MySQL
sudo systemctl start mysqld
sudo systemctl enable mysqld

4. Find Temporary Root Password
sudo grep 'temporary password' /var/log/mysqld.log

5. Secure Installation
sudo mysql_secure_installation

6. Login to MySQL
mysql -u root -p


Configure the mysql memory 



# --- Configuration (my.cnf or my.ini)
# For Linux: /etc/my.cnf or /etc/mysql/my.cnf
# For Windows: my.ini under MySQL install directory

[mysqld]
# Shared memory
innodb_buffer_pool_size = 2G
key_buffer_size = 64M

# Per-connection memory
sort_buffer_size = 2M
read_buffer_size = 1M
join_buffer_size = 1M
tmp_table_size = 64M
max_connections = 100

Note : After editing the config file, restart MySQL:
Linux : sudo systemctl restart mysql
Windows : net stop mysql
          net start mysql

Note : Check the current value
      SHOW VARIABLES LIKE '%buffer%';
      SHOW VARIABLES LIKE 'max_connections';

Note : 1. Global Buffers (Shared Memory)
          Allocated once, and used by all connections:

| Setting                   | Description                             | Typical value                                    |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| `innodb_buffer_pool_size` | Main memory for InnoDB data and indexes | 60–80% of total RAM (for dedicated MySQL server) |
| `key_buffer_size`         | Used by MyISAM tables (less common)     | Small unless using MyISAM                        |
| `query_cache_size`        | Usually 0 in MySQL 8 (deprecated)       | 0                                                |


